### Hadith 1:208

*Narrated Suwaid bin Al-Nu'man:*

In the year of the conquest of Khaibar I went with Allah's Apostle till
we reached Sahba,' a place near Khaibar, where Allah's Apostle offered
the 'Asr prayer and asked for food. Nothing but Sawrq was brought. He
ordered it to be moistened with water. He and all of us ate it and the
Prophet got up for the evening prayer (Maghrib prayer), rinsed his mouth
with water and we did the same, and he then prayed without repeating the
ablution.

